        <!-- Security FAQ -->
        <section class="content-section">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>Security Questions</h2>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Can your employees see my bank statements?</h3>
                    <p>No. Our system is designed with zero-knowledge architecture. Employees cannot access uploaded files, even for support purposes. All processing is fully automated.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Do you keep logs of my transactions?</h3>
                    <p>We only log technical metadata (file size, processing time) for system monitoring. We never log transaction details, amounts, or any financial information from your statements.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>What if I accidentally upload the wrong file?</h3>
                    <p>Files are automatically deleted after 60 minutes. You cannot retrieve files once uploaded. For immediate deletion, contact support with your session ID.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Is your service PCI compliant?</h3>
                    <p>While we don't process payments, we follow PCI DSS security standards for handling sensitive financial data.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>How do you ensure server security?</h3>
                    <p>Our servers are hosted on AWS with:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) isolation</li>
                        <li>Web Application Firewall (WAF)</li>
                        <li>DDoS protection</li>
                        <li>Regular security patches and updates</li>
                        <li>Intrusion detection systems</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

